ntal studies programs, Sarah Jaquette Ray has created an "existential tool kit" for the climate generation. Combining insights from psychology, sociology, social movements, mindfulness, and the environmental humanities, Ray explains why and how we need to let go of eco-guilt, resist burnout, and cultivate resilience while advocating for climate justice. A Field Guide to Climate Anxiety is the essential guidebook for the climate generation-and perhaps the rest of us-as we confront the greatest environmental threat of our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEnvironmental justice. 0aEnvironmentalistsxPsychology. 7aSCIENCE / Global Warming & Climate Change.2bisacsh  aEcoLit.  aanxiety.  abooks for gen z.  aburnout.  aclimate change.  aenvironmental studies.  aglobal warming.  agreen guilt.  agreta thunberg.  ahow to save the planet.  anavigating crisis.  aself care for activists.  asocial justice.  asustainable future.  ataking action.  ayouth movements.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070480808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2020z9783110704600oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520974722zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520974722423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520974722.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PAC